Two traffic wardens have been gunned down in Hammarsdale in KZN on Tuesday morning. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Two traffic wardens have been gunned down in Hammarsdale in KwaZulu-Natal on Tuesday morning. They had been travelling to work when attackers opened fire on their vehicles. eThekwini Metro Police Senior Superintendent Parbo Sewpersad said they have very little information at the moment as the scene is still active. The Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation and SAPS are reportedly on the scene for further investigations. Two traffic wardens have been gunned down in Hammarsdale in KwaZulu-Natal on Tuesday morning. Courtesy of #DStv403